Oh Cook, when will it end?  The nearest Kinko's to my house is about 5 miles away, sorry, you just lied again.  A recon marine buddy lives by me, so what, except you don't have a clue as to where I live. Opps, another lie. I have 6 or 7 offices, all listed in various telephone books, if that is what you are referring to, even one in Riverside on Brockton, must be right near your trailer park.<br><br>
Seems like the tide is turning back to &quot;normalacy&quot; except for Mr. Barela, and I hope so. Thank you Class Lass for being fair.  As for me, let me leave you all with a satire of a song as its time for me to get off this firing range, cause I just don't think one or two of you will stop, or can stop. <br><br>
The above post from Cook is so grandiose, so wild and filed with either self importance or utter delusional thinking, that until &quot;your side&quot; can talk sense to him b/c, I don't want to be anywhere near him. Of course he will take this as a sign of either (1) his victory, (2) my cowardly retreat, (3) both, or God Knows what. Now he is implying that he controls the publishing industry too.?  At least Cook finds me amusing, I think he is completely gone, i.e. pathological, but that &quot;your sides&quot; problem. I won't engage him anymore, I don't need the obsessional love/hatred that he uses and I think he is quite capable of irrational and dangerous behavior in the real world, not just in cyberspace.<br><br>
&quot;What a Wonderful Web<br><br>
